<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1016" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1016">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Peirce</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraph rase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-08"><hi rend="italic">September 8,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[Mr. Peirce reports the signature at noon this day of the protocol of the
                            arbitration of the claims of United States citizens for the seizure by
                            Russia of vessels in the North Pacific]</p>
